  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "If after deploying a chart, you (or a process) delete one of the attached resources, the command `helm status` fails instead of showing the list of existing resources excluding the one that was deleted.\r\n\r\nExample:\r\n\r\nInstall the redis chart:\r\n\r\n```\r\nhelm install -n miguel-redis stable/redis\r\nNAME:   miguel-redis\r\nLAST DEPLOYED: Wed Mar 15 17:39:38 2017\r\nNAMESPACE: miguel\r\nSTATUS: DEPLOYED\r\n\r\nRESOURCES:\r\n==> v1/Secret\r\nNAME                TYPE    DATA  AGE\r\nmiguel-redis-redis  Opaque  1     5s\r\n\r\n==> v1/PersistentVolumeClaim\r\nNAME                STATUS  VOLUME                                    CAPACITY  ACCESSMODES  AGE\r\nmiguel-redis-redis  Bound   pvc-fb53b9d9-099d-11e7-a44f-066240e9c8ba  8Gi       RWO          5s\r\n\r\n==> v1/Service\r\nNAME                CLUSTER-IP      EXTERNAL-IP  PORT(S)   AGE\r\nmiguel-redis-redis  100.65.251.209  <none>       6379/TCP  3s\r\n\r\n==> extensions/v1beta1/Deployment\r\nNAME                DESIRED  CURRENT  UP-TO-DATE  AVAILABLE  AGE\r\nmiguel-redis-redis  1        1        1           0          3s\r\n```\r\n\r\nDelete for example the associated service:\r\n```\r\nkubectl delete svc miguel-redis-redis\r\nservice \"miguel-redis-redis\" deleted\r\n```\r\n\r\n`helm status` returns an error:\r\n\r\n```\r\nhelm status miguel-redis\r\nError: services \"miguel-redis-redis\" not found\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\nIn my opinion, the output should have been the list of existing resources marking the service as `<deleted>`.",
